          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`reject_symlinks_from_root` now delegates through the shared `reject_symlinks_below` mapper, which converts every `InvalidInput` from the underlying stat path into `SymlinkFound`. That mapping is only justified below for validated catalogue/baseline filenames, but this method validates untrusted root paths and its contract says unexpected stat failures should be `Io`. A malformed root path that produces `InvalidInput` is now misreported as a confirmed symlink, so keep the direct root walk here or introduce a structured helper that preserves the real error cause.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/fs_symlink_guard.rs",
              "line": 75,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:4cacb3d90e9ede4d82f7b39d07bcb8fb795b12de998151b4708091df1561ab72",
          "at": "2026-06-18T01:10:37Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:acacd1f8a3fc7de151fa49c205a3245002c36b8f73400e5f022c49e813eff01e",
          "at": "2026-06-18T01:16:00Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`reject_symlinks_from_root` now routes all errors through `map_infra_symlink_guard_result`, which converts every `InvalidInput` into `SymlinkFound`. That caveat is documented as acceptable only for `reject_symlinks_below` because its callers pass validated filenames, but `reject_symlinks_from_root` is the public check for an untrusted root path. A malformed path that makes `symlink_metadata` return `InvalidInput` (for example an embedded NUL on Unix) is now reported as a confirmed symlink instead of `SymlinkGuardError::Io`, violating the `SymlinkGuardPort` contract that non-`NotFound` stat failures are I/O errors. Keep the from-root path on a mapper that preserves non-symlink `InvalidInput` as `Io`, or keep the direct loop here.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/fs_symlink_guard.rs",
              "line": 74,
              "category": "error handling"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:fc14bd456ed64a11b6c58a68d45b89b6da63c4f3ba52c5b49a0695cc6f8c4a85",
          "at": "2026-06-18T01:26:48Z"
